I made these easy-to-make, naturally sweet, no-bake strawberry & almond energy balls for snack time today and they were a hit! Here’s how to make them:

Ingredients:
* 1 cup Medjool dates pit removed
* 4 large strawberries sliced 
* 3/4 cup sliced almonds 
* 1 cup rolled oats
* 1 tablespoon @tinysproutsfoods hemp hearts
* pulverized freeze-dried strawberries (optional)

Instructions:
* Combine all ingredients, except the pulverized freeze-dried strawberries in a food processor or high-speed blender 
* Pulse until the almonds are mostly broken up and there are no big chunks of dates left. Don’t over-process or blend.
* Scoop out 1 heaping tablespoon of the mixture and roll into a ball shape then roll the balls in the pulverized freeze-dried strawberries. 
* Keep In the fridge for at least 30 mins to cool or serve right away 🥰🫶🏻 enjoy!

Today’s snack recipe: Coconut Muffins 🥥🤎🤍

Ingredients
* 1/2 cup all-purpose flour
* 2 tbsps coconut flour
* 1/2 tsp baking powder
* 1/2 cup coconut milk
* 1 egg
* 1/4 cup melted butter or coconut oil
* 2-3 tbsps maple syrup
* unsweetened coconut flakes for toppings
* banana slices for toppings (optional)

Instructions 
- Preheat the oven to 350F
- Line your muffin tins with cupcake liners or coat with nonstick spray.
- whisk together all the dry ingredients ( flours, baking powder) in a medium bowl
- In another mixing bowl, combine all the wet ingredients (milk, egg, melted butter, maple syrup)
- Stir in dry ingredients into the wet ingredients just until combined.
- Divide batter among the prepared muffin tin, using 1 heaping tablespoon in each mini muffin cup, and top with coconut flakes and sliced bananas.
- Bake at 350F/180C for 24-26 min. Do a toothpick test for doneness.

Made these cookies two weeks ago or so and it was a huge hit with my toddler! And my mom- brain forgot to share the recipe with you guys, so here it is 😅 the easiest yummiest cookie you’ll make and that is only sweetened with bananas 🍌
Make these Banana almond flour cookies with me!

Ingredients:
* 2 ripe bananas, mashed
* 1 and 1/4 cups almond flour
* 1 tbsp @tinysproutsfoods hemp hearts (optional)
* 1/2 tsp baking powder

Instructions:
* Preheat your oven to 350F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper then set aside.
* In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients and stir well to combine.
* Scoop heaping tablespoons of the cookie mixture onto the lined baking sheet.
* Gently flatten the cookies by pressing lightly with a ramekin, glass, or your palm and poke the top using a fork.
* Bake the cookies at 350F for 14-16 min 
* let cool for a few minutes before serving, and enjoy!!

🫐 BAKED BLUEBERRY FRITTER BITES: baby & toddler-friendly 💙💜

RECIPE :

1 cup all purpose flour
1 tsp baking powder
pinch of salt (optional)
3/4 cups blueberries (fresh or frozen)
1 egg
1 cup (5.3 oz) blueberry Greek yogurt
4 tbsp butter, melted
2-3 tbsp maple syrup
1/2 tsp vanilla extract

- pre-heat oven to 350°F and lightly grease a mini muffin pan with non-stick cooking spray. or butter.
- in a large bowl, whisk together the wet ingredients, egg, yogurt, maple syrup, melted butter and vanilla extract.
- add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients. flour, baking powder & salt (if using) and stir until well combined. then fold in the blueberries.
- scoop the batter evenly into prepared muffin cups and bake them for 15-18 min.
additional steps: 
- after baking, remove the fritters from the (silicone) muffin tin and transfer them to a baking sheet. turn your oven to the highest setting and cook them for another 3-5 min to get that nice brown crisp sides. 
- Or you can use your air-fryer. Set it at 400F, place the fritters inside and cook for 2-3 min
- serve as is or with sugar glaze, and enjoy! 😍🙌

Dinner’s always a hit whenever I make this CRISPY SALMON (nuggets). I used to make this a lot even before my toddler started eating solids and it’s always been a family favorite! 
Rue just started liking seafood again, particularly fish and I hope I don’t jinx it 😅🤞🏼

CRISPY SALMON NUGGETS RECIPE :
• 1 lb salmon, cut into cubes
• 2 tbsps of EVOO
• 1/4 cup (kewpie) mayonnaise or honey mustard
• 1 and 1/4 cups (panko or homemade) breadcrumbs 
• 2 tbsps of everything but the bagel seasoning

Instructions:

• in a large bowl, marinate your salmon with EVOO and mayonnaise for at least 15-30 min.
• prepare the coating station by combining breadcrumbs and everything but the bagel seasoning.
• once salmon is ready, coat each piece of salmon with the breadcrumb mixture and transfer on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper or onto a plate.
• cook the salmon in the air-fryer at 400F for 8-10min or in the pre-heated oven at 400F for 12-15 minutes or until cooked through.

notes:
• for babies younger than 12 mos old, you can use Greek yogurt for the marinade (I did this when Rue was younger)
• I def prefer honey mustard to mayo but I don’t always have it on hand so mayo’s a great alternative/substitute 
• We like to serve this with teriyaki sauce 
• If you can find a salt-free everything but the bagel seasoning that’s better

Veggie-packed pasta sauce
* 1 zucchini
* 1 carrot
* 1/2 large red onion
* 2 cloves of garlic
* 1 bell pepper 
* 1 celery stalk (not shown)
* 7 baby bella mushrooms
* 1 lb ground chicken or beef
* 1 25 oz can marinara/tomato sauce
* sugar, salt, pepper to taste (optional)

~ diced your veggies finely
~ heat oil in a large saucepan, saute the onions and garlic then add the ground meat and cook until no longer pink.
~ add carrots, cook for 1 minute then add the remaining veggies. cook for about 3 min
~ add canned marinara sauce, season with 1 tsp of sugar, a dash of salt, and pepper, and let simmer until veggies are soft ans the sauce starts to thicken. You can add some pasta water if needed.

to make baked macaroni
~ 1 box 16oz elbow macaroni pasta
~ 1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese
~ 1 cup shredded cheddar cheese
~ parmesan cheese add as you like

* cook 16 oz elbow macaroni pasta as per packaging instructions 
* When pasta and sauce are cooked pre-heat oven to 450F
* Meanwhile, prepare a large baking pan and layer your pasta and pasta sauce.
* pasta, sauce then cheese. I made 2 layers in a standard-size Pyrex dish
* Bake for 10 min-12 min 

• you can use this sauce on any pasta that you like, if you have babies you can use a hand blender or any blender that you have to blend the sauce until smooth so you don’t have to worry about chunks of meat being a choking risk 🥰🫶🏻

An easy and quick weeknight (rice cooker) meal for the whole family. Ready in less than 30 min and can easily be modified for toddlers and babies. 

Chicken veggie and rice recipe:

• 2-3 boneless chicken thighs 
• 2 cups of jasmine rice, washed twice
• 2 1/2 cups water or stock
• veggies estimated 1/4 cup each 
 - carrots
 - zucchini
 - bell peppers
 - green onions (both white and green parts
 - corn kernels

• sweet soy sauce (optional)
- 2 tbsp soy sauce
- 1 tsp brown sugar

Instructions:
- wash and dice your veggies, then set aside
- slice chicken into smaller pieces or cubes, set aside
- wash rice twice or until water runs clear. 
then add 2 and 1/2 cups of water and stir in 2 tbsps of soy sauce mixture. 
- add all the remaining ingredients.
- cover and cook until the rice cooker indicates it’s done. 
- once done, give it a good stir, serve and enjoy!

~ this chicken veggies and rice recipe is customizable. you can use your choice of veggies or use 1 cup of frozen mixed veggies. 
~ I served this with a side of corn on a cob and buttered shrimp.

I was worried the recipe will not work and the batter is runnier than I expected it to be —but it worked and we absolutely loved it! we had this for snack time yesterday and we also had it for breakfast earlier 😍 here’s the recipe!

Strawberry banana chocolate chip muffins

1 large banana, mashed
1 cup chopped fresh strawberries
1 large egg
3/4 cup milk 
1/4 cup melted butter
1/4 cup maple syrup
1 1/2 cups flour
2 tsp baking powder
1 tsp vanilla extract
Chocolate chips for toppings (optional)

* Preheat the oven to 375F and line muffin tins with cupcake liners, if using. 
* In a large bowl, mash the bananas and whisk together with the wet ingredients: egg, butter, milk, maple syrup & vanilla extract

* add in the flour and baking powder, and stir until the mixture comes together, but don’t over stir.
* fold chopped strawberries, then divide the batter evenly between the muffin liners. Toss a few chocolate chips on top of each muffin. 
* bake (regular size) for 18-20 minutes. Test the center with a toothpick – it should come out clean with no wet batter. 
* allow the muffins to cool in the pan for a few minutes before serving! 

Notes:
- these are suitable for babies and toddlers just opt out chocolate chips for babies younger than 24mos. Altho My toddler had chocolates before 24 mos old it is recommended to wait until after their second birthday. 
- to store: keep in an airtight container in the fridge for 3-5 days and in the freezer for up to 3 months
- to reheat: pop them in the microwave for 10-15 sec (or thaw overnight)

Tuna cheese empanadas
Ingredients:
* 1 pack 5” empanada dough (store-bought)
* 1 can chunk light tuna in water, drained
* 1/4 cup fine diced bell pepper
* 1/4 cup fine-diced red onion
* 1/4 (or more) cup mixed frozen veggies
* 1 cup shredded cheese 
* 1/3 cup mayonnaise (or greek yogurt for babies under 12m)
* 1 tbsp butter or oil for cooking
* egg wash 

Instructions:
* heat oil in a frying pan over medium heat and cook your veggies for 1-2 min and transfer to a bowl, let slightly cool
* In the same bowl, add tuna, cheese, and mayo. mix until everything is well combined
* to assemble the empanadas add a spoonful of the filling mixture on the center of each empanada disc. don’t overfill. fold the empanada dough and seal gently with your fingers making sure to tuck in the filling. then twist and fold the edges or use a fork to press and seal. 
* brush the top of the empanadas with egg wash
* once all the empanadas are assembled, let rest (optional) in the fridge or keep in the freezer until ready to cook.
* to bake: preheat the oven to 400F and bake for 20-25 min 
* cool down before serving to your little ones and enjoy! 🥰🫶🏻

Notes: 
* You can find empanada doughs in the freezer section of the grocery stores. If you can’t find one, you can use puff pastry dough instead and cut 5” discs from it. 
* Bread is also a good alternative, just flatten out the bread before using. This is more suitable for babies because bread os softer. And might take shorter time to cook (8 min)
* You can also deep fry these empanadas.
* To freeze uncooked, lay them in a baking sheet or a plate and flash freeze for 15-20 min before transferring in a large ziploc bag or container.

Carrot Mac & Cheese

Ingredients:
* 4 oz macaroni, fussili or penne pasta (half a box) I used @enjoybrami fussili pasta 
* 1 cup shredded medium cheddar cheese 
* 1 cup milk 
* 1/2 cup finely grated carrot
* 1 tbsp butter
* 1-2 tbsp flour 
* 1/4 cup pasta water
* Pinch of salt, sugar, and pepper (optional)

Instructions:
* cook pasta until al dente, reserve 1/4 cup of pasta water. 
* create a roux. melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat. once the butter is all melted, add 1 tbsp of flour and stir until the butter and flour form a crumble. pour in the milk and stir consistently until it thickens.
* add in the carrots and the pasta water. cook for 1-2 minutes, then turn the heat to low, and then add the cheese and stir until it’s completely melted. 
* season with salt, sugar, and pepper to taste (optional). turn the heat off.
* add the cooked pasta to the sauce, stir, serve, and enjoy! 🥰🫶🏻

Thinking about fried rice right now so here’s an easy Family-friendly Dinner Idea: Beef Pepper (fried) Rice. I served it wontons & kiwi fruit for my (2 y.o toddler) 

Recipe

Ingredients
Sauce (estimated)
* 2-3 tbsp (low sodium) soy sauce
* 2 tbsp honey (no honey for babies 12m and under)
* 1 tbsp oyster sauce
* 1 tbsp of garlic powder (or minced garlic)
* 1 tsp ground black pepper (add more as desired)

Other Ingredients:
* 2 tbsp cooking oil
* 2 cups leftover white rice (or a little over 2 cups)
* 1lb of  thinly sliced or shaved beef
* half of a white onion, thinly sliced
* ½ cup canned corn kernels or frozen corn kernels
* 2 tbsp butter 
* green onions, for garnish

Instructions
* First make the sauce by combining all ingredients in a bowl and mix until well combined. then set the sauce aside. 
* time to make the beef pepper rice 
1. Heat oil in a frying pan, and cook the thinly sliced beef for 2-4 min in medium heat or until it's no longer pink. Then remove from the pan and set aside.
2. Add a little bit more oil into the frying pan then add onions and saute for 2-3 minutes or until onions start to soften
3. Once the onions have softened, add the rice, stir fry for a few minutes then add the cooked beef, corn, and sauce. stir fry until they all come together. add more ground black pepper if desired. 
4. Add the butter, stir- fry a little more until it completely melts on the rice
5. Turn the heat off, and top with sliced green onions
6. Serve and enjoy!

~suitable for 12m+ 
~ you can modify the recipe and use substitutes: 
~no honey for babies under 12m 
~ serve deconstructed for younger babies if desired and serve with corn on a cob instead of loose whole corn kernels

VEGETABLE EGGY BREAD CUP RECIPE (suitable for babies 6m+)

you need:
• 3 slices of bread
• slice of zucchini (about 2-3 inches thick)
• 2 broccoli florets (raw or cooked)
• 3 baby carrots (or a slice of carrot) 
• 1 egg
• 1/2 cup whole milk
• 1/4 cup shredded cheese + more for toppings

instructions:
• preheat the oven to 400F and prepare your muffin pan. slightly grease with butter if not using muffin liners.
• prep your veggies by finely grating the zucchini & carrots. then chop the broccoli florets finely.
• in a shallow bowl, toss and combine veggies, egg, cheese & milk and set aside
• then, slice your bread into small squares/pieces and add to the same bowl. mix until every piece of bread is well coated with the egg mixture.
• scoop and divide the bread mixture filling each muffin cup. top with more cheese if desired
• bake for 15-16 min
• let cool before serving to little ones, and enjoy! 🥰

Quick & easy blueberry biscuits for breakfast today; with only 4 ingredients! Here’s the recipe 

Suitable from 12m
Ingredients:
* 1 cup self-rising flour
* 1/4 cup cold butter
* 6 tbsps milk (+more if needed)
* 1/2 cup fresh or frozen blueberries (I used @superfreshgrowers blueberries)

Instructions:
1. preheat your oven to 425 degrees.
2. slice cold butter into smaller cubes
3. in a bowl, combine flour and butter until small clumps form, and then add milk. stir with a spatula or knead with your hands until soft dough forms. fold in blueberries.
4. place dough on a floured surface and flatten. cut circular shapes using a cup or a cookie cutter. 
5. transfer them into a parchment paper lined baking sheet and bake for 9-12 minutes or until golden brown.
6. get them out of the oven and let them cool.
7. serve as is, with fruit jam, or sugar glaze, and enjoy! 

~ toss the frozen blueberries with some flour before using (which I forgot to do, but it still worked out fine)
~ if the dough becomes too sticky just add more flour. especially when kneading.

For the love of @superfreshgrowers blueberries and all things sweet for breakfast, I made these Blueberry muffin tin Dutch baby pancakes for the whole fam to enjoy!

These @superfreshgrowers blueberries, grown in the Pacific Northwest, are jam-packed with intense sweet-tart flavors, and each one is bursting with healthy nutrients. Definitely a BERRY DELICIOUS and nutritious way to start our day! 😍🫐🥞 #Ad

here’s the recipe ↓

ingredients:
- 1 cup @superfreshgrowers fresh blueberries
- 4 large eggs
- 1 cup whole milk
- 1 cup all-purpose flour
- 3 tbsp maple syrup (optional)
- 1 tsp vanilla extract
- 6 tbsp unsalted butter, melted and cooled, divided 
- toppings: powdered sugar (optional)

instructions:
- prepare your 12-well muffin tin/pan and slide it into the oven and preheat your oven to 425F. 
- combine eggs, milk, flour, sweetener, vanilla extract, pinch of salt, and 2 tbsps of melted butter in a blender and blend until smooth. only takes 30sec or less. let the batter rest for 5-10 min.
- When the oven is at the right temperature, remove the muffin tin from the oven carefully. 
- brush/pour the remainder of the melted butter into the muffin tin. add the fresh blueberries then pour about 1/4 cup of the batter into each cup/well. 
- place them on the middle rack and bake for 12-15 min or until these mini Dutch babies are puffed and golden.
- remove them from the oven, let the pancakes cool down, the middle part will sink in as it cools. 
- serve with icing sugar or syrup of choice, and enjoy!!!! 

* for babies 6m+ - opt out maple syrup and don’t forget to slice the blueberries in half or smash them before using.
* for toddlers - serve them whole, the same as you would for adults

ingredients:

- 1 tsp chicken bouillon (optional)

method:

* best served with a dipping sauce like ketchup and sweet and sour sauce

CHICKEN KARAAGE RECIPE

Ingredients:
*  1 lb boneless chicken breast or thighs
* 1/2 tsp grated ginger
* 1 tsp garlic powder or 1-2 cloves garlic, grated
* pinch of ground black pepper
* 2 tbsps soy sauce
* 2 tbsp (rice) vinegar
* 1/2 tsp sesame oil
* 1/3 cup rice flour
* 1/4 cup cornstarch 
* Oil for deep frying

Instructions:
* Pat dry chicken breast before slicing. Cut into cubes/small pieces and transfer to a bowl.
* Marinate chicken with grated ginger, garlic/garlic powder, black pepper, soy sauce, vinegar, and sesame oil —for at least 15-20 min
* In a small or shallow bowl, mix rice flour and cornstarch. Coat chicken pieces evenly with the coating mixture. 
*  Heat up cooking oil in a pot. When the cooking oil is hot enough for frying drop the chicken and cook until golden brown. Remove and transfer to a plate with a paper towel.
Additional step: I like to double fry but I use the air-fryer for the second frying. (400F 6-8 min)
* serve with (sesame mayo) dipping sauce, and enjoy these with the whole family! 😍🥰

POTATO ZUCCHINI NUGGETS RECIPE (6m)

Ingredients:
• 2 yellow potatoes
• half a zucchini, grated & squeezed (about 1 cup)
• 1 cup shredded cheese, I used Monterey jack
• 1 egg

instructions:
• bring a pot of water to a boil. meanwhile, peel (optional) and chop potatoes and boil until fork tender.
• once potatoes are cooked remove or drain the water.
• in a bowl, mash the potato until no big chunks are left, and add the rest of the ingredients. mix until well combined
• scoop 1 tbsp of the mixture and form into small nugget patties using your hands. repeat until all of the mixture is used.
• AIR FRYER METHOD: cook at 400F for 8-10 min
• OVEN METHOD: preheat to 400F and bake for 10 min or until the top starts to brown
• SHALLOW FRY: heat oil in a pan and fry on both sides for 3-5 min or until golden brown

Toddler-friendly snack/breakfast idea: PEACH MANGO KARIMAN / FRIED STUFFED BREAD OR SANDWICH 

PEACH MANGO KARIMAN RECIPE (yields 4)
ingredients:
* 4 slices of bread
* 1 egg, beaten
* 1 cup panko bread crumbs
* 1/4 cup peach mango compote (see recipe below👇 )
* 1 cup avocado oil for frying

instructions:
* remove the crust of the bread and flatten each one using a rolling pin.
* then place the filling at the center, about 1 tbsp but don’t overfill. fold the bread and seal the edges using a fork.
* dip the bread pieces in the egg mixture and then dredge with the breadcrumbs.
* heat oil over low to medium heat. then add in the bread pieces and cook until golden brown and crispy.
* transfer to a plate, LET COOL COMPLETELY BEFORE SERVING TO LITTLE ONES AND ENJOY! 🥰❤️

PEACH & MANGO COMPOTE:
Ingredients:
* 1 cup fresh or canned peaches, finely chopped
* 1 ripe mexican mango, finely chopped 
* 2 tablespoons water
* 2 tbsp maple syrup or honey (optional)
* slurry: 1 tablespoon water + 2 teaspoons cornstarch

instructions: 
* heat a small saucepan over low heat then add all the ingredients except the slurry. cook for 4-5 min stirring occasionally.
* then pour in the slurry and cook until the sauce thickens, turn heat off and let cool.
- you can store this in the fridge in a tight and sealed container for up to 2 weeks! 🥰😍🍑🥭

Lunch idea suitable for babies and toddlers - Cauliflower Alfredo pasta. Served with garlic bread knots + Strawberries and blueberries

A super easy and nutritious meal that the whole family can enjoy!
This Cauliflower Alfredo Sauce is so creamy and can be made dairy-free! Here’s the recipe:

Ingredients:
* 1 fresh head of cauliflower, cut into florets
* 2 cloves garlic peeled and minced, to taste
* 1 cup milk
* 2 cups (cauliflower) water or vegetable broth
* 3/4 cup parmesan cheese (optional)

Instructions:
* Bring a pot of water to a boil and cook the cauliflower florets for 7 min or until tender if pierced with a fork. Save 2 cups of the cauliflower water. 
* Toss all the the ingredients in the blender including the cooked cauliflower and blend until smooth and creamy.
* Pour the sauce over the pasta of your choice and enjoy!

- For leftover sauce, let it cool completely and store it in an airtight container. Keep in the fridge for up to 3 days or freeze for later use.

korean ground turkey bulgogi recipe adapted from @seonkyounglongest ground beef bulgogi ( i used honey in replacement of plum extract & sugar)

ingredients:
1 lb ground turkey
2 cloves garlic, chopped  2 stalks green onion, white and green separated 4 tbsp soy sauce  2 tbsp mirin  3 tbsp honey  1/2 tsp black pepper	 1 tbsp cooking oil	
1 tsp sesame seeds  1 tsp sesame oil

instructions:
- Combine ground turkey, garlic, white part of green onion, soy sauce, mirin, honey and black pepper in a large mixing bowl. You could marinate for 30 minutes but it’s not necessary since you’re using ground meat.
- Heat cooking oil in a pan over medium heat, add the marinated turkey mixture, stir fry and break down the meat. Keep cooking until there’s no moisture and everything is fully cooked.
- When all the moisture from the turkey is gone, toss in sesame oil and stir for a few sec then turn heat off. garnish with green parts of the green onions and sesame seeds. serve and enjoy! 🥰

I harvested a bunch of Genovese and Greek basil from my farmstand this morning and was finally able to make this baby-friendly spinach almond pesto sauce. I just love how versatile pesto is; it pairs well with pasta, pizza, sandwiches, and even toast. Originally pesto calls for pine nuts but I don’t have them so almond it is 😅

Here’s the recipe:

SPINACH ALMOND PESTO SAUCE (suitable from 6m+)

Ingredients:
• A handful of fresh Genovese basil (1.5 cup loosely packed)
• a handful of fresh baby spinach (1.5 cup loosely packed)
• 1/4 cup whole almonds 
• 1/3 cup grated parmesan cheese
• 1/2 cup olive oil (+ more if needed)
• 1 clove garlic

Instructions:
• In a blender or food processor, toss in basil leaves, baby spinach, almonds, garlic & parmesan cheese. Pulse until ingredients are well incorporated. Scrape down the sides if needed.
• Run the blender or food processor again and slowly pour the olive oil. Pulse until the mixture is smooth. Add more olive oil if desired.
• use right away or transfer into a glass container or jar for later!

SPINACH FRIED RICE RECIPE suitable from 6m (- the salt) :
 
ingredients:

- 1-2 cups fresh or frozen spinach (use more if you want it greener)
- 1/4 cup water (more if needed)

- 2 cups of (day old) rice
- 2 cloves of garlic, minced or grated
- 1 tbsp olive oil
- pinch of salt, optional

instructions:
- toss spinach and water in a blender, blend until you get a fine paste. add more if needed. mine turned out a little runny cos I used frozen spinach. but it still worked just as fine.
- heat frying pan over medium heat and drizzle the oil, then saute the garlic until fragrant. 
- add in the rice, toss for 1 minute then add the blended spinach mixture.
- cook the rice with spinach mixture until well combined. season with salt (optional) and keep cooking the rice until most of the moisture is gone. 
- serve warm or completely cooled down for little ones, and enjoy!

note: if you get a super runny paste or watery spinach mixture, just pour it on the pan first and cook until most of the moisture has evaporated and the paste starts to separate. then add oil, followed by garlic and the rice..

BANANA OAT MUFFINS RECIPE:

Ingredients:
* 3 med size bananas, mashed

* Bake the muffins for 15-16 min.

Toddler-friendly pumpkin chocolate chip bread recipe:

- 1 tsp vanilla extract 
- 2 cups self-rising flour or AP flour + 2 tsp baking powder

- then add the flour and baking powder and stir. don’t over-mix.
- stir in chocolate chips and transfer the batter into the greased or lined loaf pan. top with more chocolate chips.
- bake at 350F for 50-55 minutes

Chocolate zucchini muffins (24m+)

Ingredients
* 2 cups all-purpose flour
* 1/3 cup unsweetened cocoa powder
* 2 tsp baking powder
* 1/4 teaspoon salt
* 1/3 cup oil or unsalted melted butter
* 1/3 cup light brown sugar or maple syrup
* 2 eggs
* 1 cup shredded zucchini (from about 1 small-medium zucchini)
* 1 cup milk
* 1/2 cup regular or mini chocolate chips

Instructions:
* preheat oven to 350F and line a 12-cup muffin tin with cupcake liners
* In a large bowl, combine sugar, eggs, oil,  and milk. whisk until smooth and well combined.
* add the dry ingredients to the same bowl; flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt. Stir until just combined. Then fold in the grated zucchini and chocolate chips.
* Divide batter evenly into each muffin liner and bake for 22-24 minutes.
* Once done, let cool down, serve and enjoy! 😍🥰🫶🏻

These chocolate zucchini muffins were a hit, and the whole family loved it! We already finished half of the batch I made.

You can keep this in the fridge for 3-5 days or freeze it for up to 2 months

ingredients

* 1/2 cup + 2 tbsp whole milk
* 2 ripe bananas
* 1 egg
* 1/2 cup light brown sugar (or maple syrup)
* 1/4 cup avocado oil, or melted butter

* 2 tsp baking powder
* 1/4 tsp salt
* 1 tsp cinnamon powder ( I used @tinysproutsfoods digestion booster with apple & cinnamon)

2. In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon powder & salt stir and set aside
3. meanwhile using a blender, blend spinach, and milk until smooth

5. add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients and stir until just combined then stir in chocolate chips
6. spray a 9x5 size loaf pan with a baking spray or line with parchment paper. pour the batter. top with more chocolate chips and oats
7. bake for 55 min.

Made this super easy and delish Cinnamon Apple Fries with @eattherainbow_kids last year. If you’re looking for a fun afternoon snack for your kiddos, Try this! 😍

Cinnamon Apple Fries Recipe

What you need:
* 1-2 apples (I used @autumngloryapple )
* 1/2 cup cornstarch
* 1 tbsp cinnamon powder
*  oil for frying (i used avocado oil)

How to:
* Peel and slice the apples into wedges 
* Heat oil in a large pan over medium heat. 
* In a large bowl with a lid (or a large zip-top bag) mix together cornstarch and cinnamon powder.
* Add apple slices to the bowl, close with the lid, and shake to coat apple slices all at once.
* Fry the apple slices until golden brown on both sides. This will only take a few minutes so make sure not to burn them.
* Remove the fried apples from the pan and place them on a paper towel-lined plate.
* Serve the apple fries with your choice of dipping sauce like kinds of nut butters, caramel sauce, or whipped cream. (I served it with vanilla-flavored granola butter)

cooking with rue: peanut butter banana pancakes for snack😋🥞🍴

peanut butter pancake recipe
ingredients:
• 1 large ripe banana
• 1/2 cup milk
• 1/2 cup greek yogurt
• 1/3 cup peanut butter
• 1 egg
• 1/2 tsp vanilla extract
• 1 cup + 2 tbsp all purpose flour
• 1 tsp baking powder

instructions:
• in a bowl, mash the banana
• add egg, milk, yogurt, peanut butter & vanilla extract. stir well to combine
• then add the flour and baking powder and stir until just combined
• heat a non-stick pan or pancake griddle over medium-low heat. 
• add 1-2 tbsp of pancake batter onto the pan, cook 1 side until small bubbles start to appear, flip and cook the other side for another min or 2.
• serve and enjoy!!!
